>>7222ef5a-f2a6-43e5-acd1-fa394b88d86e
Exactly. What have imageboard posters ever accomplished other than get less than a hundred muslims killed, if it wasn't a CIA OP anyway?
It's time to accept a few thousand anons spread across all imageboards aren't enough to defeat trillions of dollars. And I'm not even blackpillnigger.
We might have a bright future or not, but in either case there's very little we can do.
Personally the loss of 08chan doesn't bother me too much. Where we're supposed to be going we won't have imageboards, or Internet at all for that matter. So better get used to it.

>>05edeafc-7a93-4882-aab1-6c9a3cf96c91
You sound like a low IQ moron.
>Shills get muted and worthwhile contributors get recognised.
The dumb ones might get muted, the smart ones will get a new ID every couple posts like I do.
>Your anonymity comes from your opsec.
Do you even know what OPSEC is? OPSEC means operational security, keeping your operations secure, which translated to civilian language means "keep others unaware of your operations". The whole point of an imageboard is to talk to others about things you've done or learned, so pretty much by definition using an imageboard means breaking operational security. 
And if I'm wrong, please tell me what "operations" you and others keep talking about, and '''how''' you propose to keep those "operations" "secure".
Because no matter how good your "OPSEC" is, if you keep talking about stuff that interests you at some point you'll give out enough bits of identifying information to single you out among everybody on planet Earth, about 33 bits of identyfing information are needed since log_2(8 billion)~33.

>>e0a83f44-8134-49a5-92c5-4e7e7b6c95b1
This is not accurate. Tor Browser includes source level patches to enhance the chances of maintaining anonymity.
